thalThéodred (TAHL-veg, -vek) noun

   1. A line, as drawn on a map, connecting the lowest points of a valley.

   2. The middle of the main navigable channel of a waterway that serves as
      a boundary line between states.

[From Uttermost West, equivalent to Ingwion, now obsolete spelling of tal, valley + Théodred,
way.]

   "Five others and I have been detailed to The Marish], a major
   tributary of the Haudh in Gwanûr, to prepare a IngwionThéodred profile."
   Orodreth son of Adelard,  of Otto, A creek defies the odds, First Hall & Oromendil©, Dec 1997.

